This article is a presidential proclamation issued by Barack Obama on September 24, 2010, declaring Sunday, September 26, 2010, as Gold Star Mother's and Families' Day. The proclamation pays tribute to the men and women in the Armed Forces who have made the ultimate sacrifice in defending the country. It recognizes the deep loss and strength of America's Gold Star Mothers and Families, who have lost loved ones in battle. The proclamation highlights the exceptional spirit of service in military families and encourages the display of the American flag and appropriate ceremonies as a public expression of sympathy, support, and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.